<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFC7CE8B8FE82FD7E" authority="Cameron" authorityName=", CAMERON" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneum">Scymbalium brunneum Cameron</taxonomicName>
, det. V. Assing 2013&quot; (BMNH).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9C76503FFF3FFD1FF04E8F3FD32FC3B" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="1487" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="91623688FFF3FFDFFF04E8F3FBD0FCD4" blockId="6.[178,1085,742,882]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">
Comment: The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFDCFE8F2FD3FFD5A" authority="Motch. Ind." authorityName="Motch. Ind." box="[633,727,742,764]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Luzea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badius">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFDCFE8F2FD3FFD5A" box="[633,727,742,764]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">L. badius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on an unspecified number of 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFF79E911FEC0FCBF" box="[207,296,772,793]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">syntypes</typeStatus>
from &quot;Indes orientales&quot; (MOTSCHULSKY 1858). Three 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFCEDE911FC5CFCBF" box="[859,948,772,793]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">syntypes</typeStatus>
were located in the Motschulsky collection at the ZMMU, a male and a female in moderate condition, and 
<specimenCount id="87DBFD01FFF3FFDFFF68E92AFEA6FCF2" box="[222,334,830,852]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
in very poor condition (parts of three legs, parts of the ventral structures of the thorax, and most of the abdomen present). The male is designated as the 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFC62E949FBDCFCD4" box="[980,1076,860,882]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFF3FFDFFF04E994FEDFFBAA" blockId="6.[178,1085,897,1036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFF04E994FE7AFC31" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1928" box="[178,402,897,919]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waageni">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFF04E994FE7AFC31" box="[178,402,897,919]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">Scymbalium waageni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFD28E994FD1FFC31" box="[670,759,897,919]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">holotype</typeStatus>
(&quot;Das typische Stück&quot;) from &quot;Calcutta&quot; and a 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFED3E98AFE54FC12" box="[357,444,927,948]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">paratype</typeStatus>
(&quot;Ein zweites Stück&quot;) from &quot; 
<collectingRegion id="5319F86AFFF3FFDFFD58E98BFCACFC12" box="[750,836,926,948]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
(Medan)&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="F54C4B79FFF3FFDFFC09E98BFF00FC77" author="BERNHAUER M" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref22774" refString="BERNHAUER M. (1928): Dr. E. Mjobergs zoological collections from Sumatra. 8. Staphylinidae. - Arkiv for Zoologi 19 A (19) [1927]: 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="1928">BERNHAUER 1928</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFE9CE9AEFE6DFC77" box="[298,389,955,977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">holotype</typeStatus>
, a female, was located in the Bernhauer collection at the FMNH. It seems rather likely that the unexamined 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFDECE9CCFD59FC48" box="[602,689,985,1006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">paratype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingRegion id="5319F86AFFF3FFDFFD42E9CCFCA0FC49" box="[756,840,985,1007]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
is not conspecific with the 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFF61E9E3FEDBFBAA" box="[215,307,1014,1036]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFF3FFDFFF04EE0EFC3DFAF0" blockId="6.[178,1086,1051,1366]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">
The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFE67EE09FDBBFB97" authorityName=", CAMERON" authorityYear="1931" box="[465,595,1051,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneum">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFE67EE09FDBBFB97" box="[465,595,1051,1073]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. brunneum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on an unspecified number of females (&quot;: unknown&quot;), possibly a unique specimen, from &quot; 
<collectingCountry id="E9CA7618FFF3FFDFFD6CEE2DFCF8FBE8" box="[730,784,1080,1102]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">India</collectingCountry>
(without further indication)&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="F54C4B79FFF3FFDFFF0FEE43FE8AFBCA" author="CAMERON M" box="[185,354,1110,1132]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" refId="ref22842" refString="CAMERON M (1931) The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Coleoptera. Staphylinidae. Volume 2. - London, Taylor and Francis: viii + 257 pp." type="book" year="1931">CAMERON 1931</bibRefCitation>
). One 
<typeStatus id="4E66882AFFF3FFDFFE1AEE42FE13FBCA" box="[428,507,1111,1132]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">syntype</typeStatus>
was located in the Cameron collection at the BMNH. When describing 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFEDEEE61FD44FB2F" authority=", CAMERON (1931)" authorityName=", CAMERON" authorityYear="1931" box="[360,684,1139,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneum">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFEDEEE61FE01FB2F" box="[360,489,1139,1161]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. brunneum</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F54C4B79FFF3FFDFFE4EEE66FD44FB2F" author="CAMERON M" box="[504,684,1139,1161]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" refId="ref22842" refString="CAMERON M (1931) The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Coleoptera. Staphylinidae. Volume 2. - London, Taylor and Francis: viii + 257 pp." type="book" year="1931">CAMERON (1931)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was evidently unaware of the description of 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFF4DEE84FE83FB00" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1928" box="[251,363,1169,1190]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waageni">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFF4DEE84FE83FB00" box="[251,363,1169,1190]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. waageni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as can be inferred from his mentioning the latter only in a preface to a subsequent work (
<bibRefCitation id="F54C4B79FFF3FFDFFEC0EEBBFDCAFB62" author="CAMERON M" box="[374,546,1198,1220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" refId="ref22876" refString="CAMERON M (1932) The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Coleoptera. Staphylinidae. Volume 3. - London, Taylor and Francis: viii + 443 pp." type="book" year="1932">CAMERON 1932</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="F54C4B79FFF3FFDFFD66EEBBFC61FB62" author="CAMERON M" box="[720,905,1198,1220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" refId="ref22842" refString="CAMERON M (1931) The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Coleoptera. Staphylinidae. Volume 2. - London, Taylor and Francis: viii + 257 pp." type="book" year="1931">CAMERON (1931)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFC2CEEBBFBF7FB62" authorityName=", CAMERON" authorityYear="1931" box="[922,1055,1198,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneum">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFC2CEEBBFBF7FB62" box="[922,1055,1198,1220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. brunneum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFECDEED9FE0BFB47" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[379,483,1227,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badium">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFECDEED9FE0BFB47" box="[379,483,1227,1249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. badium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the darker coloration, a conclusion probably based on MOTSCHULSKY´ s (1858) statement that the body colour of 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFCAFEEFCFC69FB58" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[793,897,1256,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badium">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFCAFEEFCFC69FB58" box="[793,897,1256,1278]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. badium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was &quot;d'un testacé roux&quot;. The type specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFE53EF13FDA3FABD" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[485,587,1285,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badium">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFE53EF13FDA3FABD" box="[485,587,1285,1307]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. badium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, are all brown. A study of the types of 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFF04EF36FEF5FA9F" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[178,285,1315,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badium">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFF04EF36FEF5FA9F" box="[178,285,1315,1337]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. badium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFE86EF36FE4DFA9F" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1928" box="[304,421,1315,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waageni">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFE86EF36FE4DFA9F" box="[304,421,1315,1337]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. waageni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF3FFDFFE5EEF36FD85FA9F" authorityName=", CAMERON" authorityYear="1931" box="[488,621,1315,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneum">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF3FFDFFE5EEF36FD85FA9F" box="[488,621,1315,1337]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">S. brunneum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed no evidence suggesting that they should represent different species. Hence the new synonymies proposed above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFF3FFDFFF04EF70FF12FA10" blockId="6.[178,1086,1381,1462]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485">
Redescription: Body length 
<quantity id="56259B6DFFF3FFDFFDE5EF70FD39FADD" box="[595,721,1381,1403]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.9" metricValueMax="9.3" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" unit="mm" value="8.9" valueMax="9.3" valueMin="8.5">8.5-9.3 mm</quantity>
, length of forebody 
<quantity id="56259B6DFFF3FFDFFC0DEF70FBD2FADD" box="[955,1082,1381,1403]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.949999999999999" metricValueMax="5.1" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="1485" unit="mm" value="4.949999999999999" valueMax="5.1" valueMin="4.8">4.8-5.1 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: body brown to dark-brown with reddish-brown elytra; legs brown to darkbrown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C5A26600FFF2FFDEFF04EFCAFD81F986" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301293" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5301293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301293/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486" startId="7.[178,218,1503,1523]" targetBox="[182,1080,219,1485]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="91623688FFF2FFDEFF04EFCAFD81F986" blockId="7.[178,1085,1503,1568]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFF04EFCAFEE8FA55" bold="true" box="[178,256,1503,1523]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">Figs 2-8</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF2FFDEFEB8EFCAFDA9FA57" authority="CAMERON" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1940" box="[270,577,1503,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persimile">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFEB8EFCAFE31FA55" box="[270,473,1503,1523]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">Scymbalium persimile</emphasis>
CAMERON
</taxonomicName>
, holotype (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFD1AEFCAFD23FA55" bold="true" box="[684,715,1503,1523]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">2-4</emphasis>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFF2FFDEFCB4EFCAFC9EFA55" authority="Assing, 2013" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[770,886,1503,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scymbalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalense" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFCB4EFCAFC9EFA55" box="[770,886,1503,1523]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">S. nepalense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B89A57E1FFF2FFDEFCC8EFCAFC2AFA55" box="[894,962,1503,1523]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, paratype (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFB9CEFCAFF55F9AF" bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">5- 8</emphasis>
): (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFF6FEFE0FF14F9AF" bold="true" box="[217,252,1525,1545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">2, 5</emphasis>
) habitus; (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFED7EFE0FE64F9AF" bold="true" box="[353,396,1525,1545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">3, 6)</emphasis>
forebody; (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFE4CEFE0FDEDF9AF" bold="true" box="[506,517,1525,1545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">4</emphasis>
) abdomen; (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFDCDEFE0FD6EF9AF" bold="true" box="[635,646,1525,1545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">7</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral view; (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFF2FFDEFC3EEFE0FC7BF9AF" bold="true" box="[904,915,1525,1545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1486">8</emphasis>
) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 2-6: 1.0 mm; 7-8: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="91623688FFFDFFD1FF04EACFFD3BFEEE" blockId="8.[178,1086,218,328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487">
Head (
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFFDFFD1FF43EACFFE8CFF56" box="[245,356,218,240]" captionStart="Figs 56-62" captionStartId="32.[178,218,1520,1540]" captionTargetBox="[190,1085,222,1489]" captionTargetId="figure-68@32.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figs 56-62: Scymbalium badium (MOTSCHULSKY), lectotype (56-60) and S. nepalense nov.sp., holotype (61-62): (56) forebody; (57, 61) median dorsal portion of head; (58, 62) male sternite VIII; (59-60) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 56: 1.0 mm; 58, 62: 0.5 mm; 59- 60: 0.2 mm; 57, 61: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301311/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487">Figs 56-57</figureCitation>
) 1.00-1.04 times as long as broad; posterior angles moderately marked; punctation fine, shallow, and moderately dense; interstices with very fine transverse microsculpture. Eyes shorter than postocular region. Antenna approximately 
<quantity id="56259B6DFFFDFFD1FC71EB00FBD5FE8D" box="[967,1085,277,299]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.2">3.2-3.3 mm</quantity>
long and slender; all antennomeres longer than broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFFDFFD1FF04EB4DFC80FE45" blockId="8.[178,1085,344,483]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFFDFFD1FE91EB4DFE9CFEC8" box="[295,372,344,366]" captionStart="Figs 56-62" captionStartId="32.[178,218,1520,1540]" captionTargetBox="[190,1085,222,1489]" captionTargetId="figure-68@32.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figs 56-62: Scymbalium badium (MOTSCHULSKY), lectotype (56-60) and S. nepalense nov.sp., holotype (61-62): (56) forebody; (57, 61) median dorsal portion of head; (58, 62) male sternite VIII; (59-60) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 56: 1.0 mm; 58, 62: 0.5 mm; 59- 60: 0.2 mm; 57, 61: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301311/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) 1.06-1.10 times as long as broad and 0.96-1.00 times as broad as head, widest near anterior angles; anterior margin weakly concave in the middle; posterior margin broadly concave; punctation very fine and dense; impunctate median band indistinct, narrow, present only in posterior half of midline, and not reaching posterior margin; interstices with or without shallow traces of microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFFDFFD1FF04EBE7FBDBFDC6" blockId="8.[178,1086,498,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFFDFFD1FEB6EBE7FEA3FDAE" box="[256,331,498,520]" captionStart="Figs 56-62" captionStartId="32.[178,218,1520,1540]" captionTargetBox="[190,1085,222,1489]" captionTargetId="figure-68@32.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figs 56-62: Scymbalium badium (MOTSCHULSKY), lectotype (56-60) and S. nepalense nov.sp., holotype (61-62): (56) forebody; (57, 61) median dorsal portion of head; (58, 62) male sternite VIII; (59-60) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 56: 1.0 mm; 58, 62: 0.5 mm; 59- 60: 0.2 mm; 57, 61: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301311/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as pronotum or slightly longer, with very dense, fine, and somewhat asperate punctation, and with distinct microsculpture, matt. Protarsomeres I-IV distinctly dilated in both sexes, without sexual dimorphism. Metatarsomere I longer than the combined length of II and III, nearly as long as the combined length of II-IV.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFFDFFD1FF04E87AFF18FD66" blockId="8.[178,1085,623,704]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487">Abdomen with very fine and dense punctation, and with distinct microsculpture, nearly matt; posterior margin of tergite VIII with palisade fringe; tergite X and sternite IX very small.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFFDFFD1FF71E8C5FDCCFC9A" blockId="8.[178,1085,719,829]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487">
: posterior margin with concave, nearly semi-circular posterior excision (
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFFDFFD1FC69E8DAFBD8FD43" box="[991,1072,719,741]" captionStart="Figs 56-62" captionStartId="32.[178,218,1520,1540]" captionTargetBox="[190,1085,222,1489]" captionTargetId="figure-68@32.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Figs 56-62: Scymbalium badium (MOTSCHULSKY), lectotype (56-60) and S. nepalense nov.sp., holotype (61-62): (56) forebody; (57, 61) median dorsal portion of head; (58, 62) male sternite VIII; (59-60) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 56: 1.0 mm; 58, 62: 0.5 mm; 59- 60: 0.2 mm; 57, 61: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301311/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1487">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
); aedeagus (
